PROCEDURE:
1. Map the directory structure and identify all feature modules.
2. Find and read all test configuration files.
3. Count and categorize test files by type (unit, integration, e2e).
4. Read a representative sample of test files from each category.
5. Identify features that lack tests entirely.
6. Review CI/CD configuration for test execution.
7. Check for flaky tests (retry logic, timeouts, skipping).
8. Compile the report.

Begin the QA audit now.
